<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-09-25T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-09-25T17:00:00-05:00" n="240" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d240">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">711.689 Entry, Residence and
                            Establishment/6: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Greece</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">MacVeagh</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-09-25T18:00:00-04:00">September 25, 1936—6
                                    p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>53. Your 96, September 24, noon. Department relies upon Legation to
                            assure that Greek and English texts will be exactly identic in meaning.
                            Full powers being forwarded.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p>[For text of treaty, signed at Athens, November 21, 1936, see
                                Department of State Treaty Series No. 930, or 51 Stat. 230.]</p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>